<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: TRW/ROSS-TAS 40, 55, 65 AND 85 - ASSEMBLE - WORM PRELOAD ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0500316" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="3">
        <title>WORM PRELOAD ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With adjusting screw jam nut loose, turn sector shaft adjusting screw clockwise to provide
                45 to 50 in-lbs. (5 to 5.5 N&#8226;m) of torque required to rotate the input shaft, valve/worm assembly
                through one half turn (180&#176;) each side of center (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500386">Figure 86</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500386" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500386" filename="../figg05/G0500386.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 86. Turn Sector Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This procedure will properly mesh and seat the rack piston and sector shaft teeth for final
                        adjustments.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn sector shaft adjusting screw counterclockwise one half turn and note maximum torque
                required to rotate the input shaft, valve/worm assembly through one half turn (180&#176;) each side of
                center (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500387">Figure 87</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500387" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500387" filename="../figg05/G0500387.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 87. Note Maximum Torque</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust sector shaft adjusting screw clockwise to increase maximum torque noted in step 2 by
                7 in-lbs. (0.8 N&#8226;m). Tighten jam nut firmly against side cover while holding the adjusting screw
                in position. Tighten jam nut to 43 ft-lbs. (58 N&#8226;m) and check input shaft, valve/worm assembly
                torque again. Re-adjust if input shaft torque exceeds 40 in-lbs. (4.5 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500388">Figure 88</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500388" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500388" filename="../figg05/G0500388.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 88. Adjust Torque</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
